Ok...I have been meaning to address this. &lt;clears voice&gt; Shaman and Clerics are not tanks!  AC is great and all, but wisdom is your god.  True, shaman and clerics can melee decently up until around lvl 25, but after that, they become more and more group reliant.  There role is mainly that of the healer and buffer and occasionally the nuker(dependent on situation).  You may be thinking to yourself, &quot;But Oake, why would they give me such pretty armor if it was not what I really needed...&quot;  well I say to that, this is armor that is somewhat easily obtainable to you in the mid 20s and very easily questable by 30.  So why would they give you your best armor at such a young age, friend.  They didn't.  Totemic will soon be replaced by other items.  Most of the shaman that I know that wear totemic do it for the looks.  &quot;But Oake, I can take hits well, how do you really know I am a caster???&quot;  Simple, you get a pet...therefore you're no longer the main source of melee power...why would they give a pet to a melee class?  &quot;Oake, you're a druid...you don't know what you're talking about...&quot;  &lt;sigh&gt; I am a druid, but I do have dreams of living a life where I was a shaman...oh I did play well at least to my 25th season...(my that was long ago).  Anyways, to all shaman and clerics(pet peeve...don't mean to harp), once you start to get older and you're grouped with that warrior, let him hit...he does it so much better than you do.  sit back and take a support role...meditate for that extra heal or that extra nuke.  It could mean the difference in the game...so in short, learn to stay out the mix and meditate when you can.  In groups at upper levels, this will be expected of you as it is me.  Our powers come from our magic...not from our muscles. (even those big barb muscles).  &lt;puts the soap box back in the corner&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http: